    <abstract>
      <p>Pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics (PKPD) are key considerations in any study of molecular therapies. It is thus imperative to factor their effects into any <italic toggle="yes">in silico</italic> model of biological tissue involving such therapies. Furthermore, creating a standardized and flexible framework will benefit the community by increasing access to such modules and enhancing their communicability. PhysiCell is an open-source physics-based cell simulator, i.e., a platform for modeling biological tissue, that is quickly being adopted and utilized by the mathematical biology community. We present here PhysiPKPD, an open-source PhysiCell-based package that allows users to include PKPD in PhysiCell models.</p>
      <sec specific-use="heading-level-1" id="s0001">
        <title>Availability &amp; Implementation</title>
        <p>The source code for PhysiPKPD is located here: <ext-link xlink:href="https://github.com/drbergman/PhysiPKPD" ext-link-type="uri" specific-use="url">https://github.com/drbergman/PhysiPKPD</ext-link>. </p>
      </sec>
    </abstract>
